options.text: "The younger generations are bored with the current offerings," says recently-graduated psychologist @@RANDOM_NAME@@, as @@HE/SHE@@ looks up from @@HIS/HER@@ phone for a split second. "When I visit the Museum of @@DEMONYM_ADJECTIVE@@ History, I don't just want to stare at some ancient objects. What we really need is interaction, and the best way to provide this is through technology. Children are more eager to learn when you use video clips and games to explain history. Imagine being chased by holographic velociraptors at the Museum of Natural History! That would be money well spent, in my opinion."
